		<td><b>Re: 3D Nes Emulator</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />No, the 3d scene rendering is based on automatic &quot;on the fly&quot; analysis of 2d scene. I don't follow the approach of HD Nes. This approach requires huge amount of graphic work done to let just a game played. You can see that when an object is rendered for the first time, the game become a little lag due to the analysis computation.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


